The CLI command `showrunner git stage-story` tries to stage these directories but .gitignore blocks them.

PART 1 — Add a comment to the root .gitignore explaining the distinction:
At the top of .gitignore, add:
  # ─── Showrunner Tool Repository ────────────────────────
  # This .gitignore is for the TOOL SOURCE CODE repository.
  # Story project directories are excluded here because they
  # are user content, not tool code.  
  # When you create a story project with `showrunner init`,
  # it generates its own .gitignore that TRACKS story files.

