Find the project initialization code. It's likely in:
  - src/showrunner_tool/commands/init.py (or init_cmd.py)
  - src/showrunner_tool/core/ somewhere

When a new story project is initialized, it should create a project-level .gitignore:

# Showrunner Story Project
# Story YAML files are tracked (they ARE the content)

# System databases (auto-rebuilt from YAML on startup)
*.db
*.db-journal
*.db-wal

# Vector store (rebuilt from YAML)
.chroma/

# Python/Node artifacts
__pycache__/
node_modules/
.next/
*.pyc

# IDE/OS artifacts
.DS_Store
.idea/
.vscode/

# Showrunner temp files
.showrunner/chat.db
.showrunner/sessions/*.tmp

If init.py doesn't exist or the init is done differently, check CLAUDE.md and README.md 
to understand how projects are initialized, then add the .gitignore generation there.

