  cascadeUpdate: (body: { file_path: string; dry_run?: boolean }) =>
    post<any>("/api/v1/cascade/update", body),

PART 4 — Integrate into Zen Mode:
Find the Zen Mode save flow. Look at:
  - src/web/src/hooks/useAutoSave.ts  
  - src/web/src/components/zen/ZenEditor.tsx (or similar)
  - The zenSlice in whichever store file handles Zen Mode

After a fragment is saved successfully, show a toast notification using sonner:
  import { toast } from 'sonner';

  // After successful save:
  toast("Scene saved", {
    description: "Run cascade update to sync related entities?",
    action: {
      label: "Update",
      onClick: async () => {
        try {
          const result = await api.cascadeUpdate({ 
            file_path: `fragment/${sceneSlug}.yaml`,
            dry_run: false 
          });
          toast.success(`Updated ${result.entities_updated} entities`);
        } catch (err) {
          toast.error("Cascade update failed");
        }
      },
    },
  });

If the save flow doesn't have a clear place for this, add it as a button in the 
Zen Mode toolbar instead.

VERIFICATION:
- curl -X POST http://localhost:8000/api/v1/cascade/update \
    -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
    -d '{"file_path": "fragment/test.yaml", "dry_run": true}'
  Should return a JSON response (even if empty results)
- cd src/web && npx next build passes
- The cascade router is registered in app.py

Commit: git add -A && git commit -m "feat: cascade update REST API + Zen Mode integration (Phase L track 3)"
```

